<p>A post shared by <a href="https://www.instagram.com/oprah/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading"> Oprah</a> (@oprah) on Mar 21, 2020 at 7:19pm PDT</p>
<p><a href="https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/first-tom-hanks-and-now-idris-elba-twitter-has-had-it-with-coronavirus-2195921">Speaking of his wife Sabrina's decision to stay with him,</a>
 Idris, in a video shared by him last week, said, "Sabrina wanted to be 
by my side, as much as we talked about her not coming to where I am, she
 did, and wanted to. I love her even more for it and I would do the same
 for her." The actor added that he wanted to keep his wife safe and 
added, "So, we calculated that risk and decided to be together... I hope
 you guys can understand it."</p>
